We require change management in the OnDemand version of jira. I would like to be able to create workflows that have approval steps requiring approval from multiple users. For example in an issue type 'product change request' the workflow might require an approval from at least one user in the QA management group, at least one user in the Engineering group, at least on user in the production management group, and the CEO. For another issue type 'QC procedure change' the workflow might require an approval stage only requiring one user in the QA management group. This would really extend the useful capabilities of Jira OnDemand and make it useful to our organisation. In fact as a recent subscriber to the OnDemand service I am surprised and a bit disappointed not to find this level of functionality.

I left this comment on issue JRA-6182 but as that is a very old issue and was generated in relation to an older installed version of JIRA i though it sensible to create the issue afresh.

I notice that the issue has been resolved for customers using the installed version of JIRA via an add-on "Group Sign-Off for JIRA". If I had known this at the time of starting to use JIRA I would have probably progressed down the installed route...

